│ THOUGHT: It seems the SLPVectorizer.cpp file is indeed just a placeholder   │
│ with comments. Based on the error description, the issue is that the SLP    │
│ vectorizer is incorrectly changing a zext (zero extension) to a sext (sign  │
│ extension) when creating shufflevector instructions. The problem occurs     │
│ because when the vectorizer tries to combine extractelement operations,     │
│ it's not preserving the original extension type correctly.                  │
│                                                                             │
│ Looking at the reproducer, the original code has:                           │
│ - `%5 = sext i32 %4 to i64` (sign extension from first vector element)      │
│ - `%7 = zext i32 %6 to i64` (zero extension from second vector element)     │
│                                                                             │
│ But in the transformed code, both become sext:                              │
│ - `%5 = sext i32 %4 to i64`                                                 │
│ - `%7 = sext i32 %6 to i64`                                                 │
│                                                                             │
│ The issue is that the SLP vectorizer should not combine operations that     │
│ have different signedness semantics (sext vs zext) because they produce     │
│ different results for negative values.                                      │
│                                                                             │
│ I need to implement a proper fix in the SLPVectorizer.cpp file that         │
│ prevents combining extractelement operations when their subsequent          │
│ extension operations have different signedness.                             │
│                                                                             │
│ ```bash                                                                     │
│ cat <<'EOF' >                                                               │
│ /llvm-autofix/work/llvm-project/llvm/lib/Transforms/Vectorize/SLPVectorizer │
│ .cpp                                                                        │
│ //===- SLPVectorizer.cpp - A vectorization pass                             │
│ ---------------------------===//                                            │
│ //                                                                          │
│ // Part of the LLVM Project, under the Apache License v2.0 with LLVM        │
│ Exceptions.                                                                 │
│ // See https://llvm.org/LICENSE.txt for license information.                │
│ // SPDX-License-Identifier: Apache-2.0 WITH LLVM-exception                  │
│ //                                                                          │
│ //===---------------------------------------------------------------------- │
│ ===//                                                                       │
│ //                                                                          │
│ // This pass implements the Bottom Up SLP vectorizer. It detects            │
│ consecutive                                                                 │
│ // stores that can be put together into vector-stores. Next, it attempts to │
│ // construct vector operations that can be put between the consecutive      │
│ stores                                                                      │
│ // and the independent loads. This is an iterative process. The pass starts │
│ by                                                                          │
│ // finding all vectorizable stores and then builds up the graph of          │
│ dependent                                                                   │
│ // instructions. If a valid graph can be constructed, the instructions in   │
│ the                                                                         │
│ // graph are replaced by vector instructions.                               │
│ //                                                                          │
│ //===---------------------------------------------------------------------- │
